English.Text: Before receiving the command, your doctor was already preparing to treat the officer. She had clean warm water ready to be pumped into and back out of her patient's stomach through a rubber tube she expertly passed through the tiny gap left on his swollen pharynx. The gastric lavage is successful and the officer's windpipe slowly clears out. It isn't until he's out of danger that the whole crew realises everyone had been holding their breath.
